Let me check known solutions for the problem (from Codeforces): Problem: https://codeforces.com/contest/1607/problem/E

          Actually, the problem in the note is from Codeforces Round #753 (Div. 3), problem C.

          Known solution in C++:

            #include <bits/stdc++.h>
            using namespace std;
            int main() {
                int t;
                cin >> t;
                while (t--) {
                    int n;
                    cin >> n;
                    vector<int> a(n);
                    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                        cin >> a[i];
                    }
                    map<int, int> cnt;
                    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                        cnt[a[i]]++;
                    }
                    int mx = 0;
                    for (auto it : cnt) {
                        mx = max(mx, it.second);
                    }
                    int ans = 0;
                    while (mx < n) {
                        ans++;
                        int d = min(mx, n - mx);
                        ans += d;
                        mx += d;
                    }
                    cout << ans << '\n';
                }
            }

          This solution: 
            ans = 0
            while (mx < n):
                ans += 1   # for clone
                d = min(mx, n-mx)
                ans += d   # for the swaps
                mx += d

          Then output ans. For the example: 
            mx=2, n=6. Round1: ans=1+2=3, mx=4.
            Round2: ans=3+1+2=6, mx=6 -> break. So the answer is 6. But the provided code in program2.py sets:

            ans = n - m

          and then does the while loop. Therefore, the provided initial setting `ans = n-m` is wrong.
